[_Dirofilaria immitis_ and _D. repens_ are nematodes of dogs occasionally transmitted to humans by mosquitoes of the _Culex_ family. Whether this particular nematode was _D. immitis_ or _D. repens_ can only be determined upon molecular analysis, which probably was not performed. The worm is usually not sensitive to albendazole but needs to be surgically removed. A serological test has been described (Ermakova LA et al. _Dirofilaria repens_ in the Russian Federation: current epidemiology, diagnosis, and treatment from a federal reference center perspective. Int J Infect Dis. 2014;23:47-52).

Information and a map of Kochi, Kerala, can be found here: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kochi. - Mod.EP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4089925,308.]
